137: - Use Settings to repair, reconnect, or clear provider credentials when a provider reports an error
141: - **Browser Safe Storage prompts:** Chromium-based imports may request Keychain access to decrypt browser cookies. Allow access for the signed Pinemeter app if you initiated the import.
142: - **Safari import cannot see cookies:** Grant Full Disk Access to Pinemeter in macOS System Settings, then retry the import.
143: - **Provider unavailable, rejected, or rate limited:** Open Settings and use the provider-specific repair, reconnect, or clear actions. The UI shows sanitized status and copyable error text without raw credentials.
144: - **Reset local state:** Clear the affected provider in Settings, sign in again in your browser if needed, then import or paste the credential again.
